Troubleshooting
Issue: Command not found after installation

Ensure virtual environment is activated: source ~/opsctl-project/venv/bin/activate
Reinstall: pip install -e .
Issue: Import errors

Verify all __init__.py files exist
Check Python path: python3 -c "import sys; print(sys.path)"
Issue: Permission denied on config file

Check directory permissions: ls -la ~/.opsctl/
Create directory manually: mkdir -p ~/.opsctl && chmod 755 ~/.opsctl
Issue: Arguments not parsing correctly

Verify subparser destination is set: dest='command'
Check that set_defaults(func=execute) is called for each subcommand
